name: $::type
desc: Returns: Server interaction or operation type.

name: $resource
desc: Returns: The type of the resource.  See http://hl7.org/fhir/STU3/resourcelist.html.

pvardefs.name: pValue
pvardefs.desc: The type of the resource.  See http://hl7.org/fhir/STU3/resourcelist.html.

name: $label
desc: Returns: The label would be used for tracking/logging purposes by test engines.

pvardefs.name: pValue
pvardefs.desc: The label would be used for tracking/logging purposes by test engines.

name: $description
desc: Returns: The description would be used by test engines for tracking and reporting purposes.

pvardefs.name: pValue
pvardefs.desc: The description would be used by test engines for tracking and reporting purposes.

name: $accept
desc: Returns: The content-type or mime-type to use for RESTful operation in the 'Accept' header.

pvardefs.name: pValue
pvardefs.desc: The content-type or mime-type to use for RESTful operation in the 'Accept' header.

name: $contentType
desc: Returns: The content-type or mime-type to use for RESTful operation in the 'Content-Type' header.

pvardefs.name: pValue
pvardefs.desc: The content-type or mime-type to use for RESTful operation in the 'Content-Type' header.

name: $destination
desc: Returns: The server where the request message is destined for.  Must be one of the server numbers listed in TestScript.destination section.

pvardefs.name: pValue
pvardefs.desc: The server where the request message is destined for.  Must be one of the server numbers listed in TestScript.destination section.

name: $encodeRequestUrl
desc: Returns: Whether or not to implicitly send the request url in encoded format. The default is true to match the standard RESTful client behavior. Set to false when communicating with a server that does not support encoded url paths.

pvardefs.name: pValue
pvardefs.desc: Whether or not to implicitly send the request url in encoded format. The default is true to match the standard RESTful client behavior. Set to false when communicating with a server that does not support encoded url paths.

name: $origin
desc: Returns: The server where the request message originates from.  Must be one of the server numbers listed in TestScript.origin section.

pvardefs.name: pValue
pvardefs.desc: The server where the request message originates from.  Must be one of the server numbers listed in TestScript.origin section.

name: $params
desc: Returns: Path plus parameters after [type].  Used to set parts of the request URL explicitly.

pvardefs.name: pValue
pvardefs.desc: Path plus parameters after [type].  Used to set parts of the request URL explicitly.

name: $requestHeader
desc: Returns: Header elements would be used to set HTTP headers.

name: $addrequestHeader
desc: Header elements would be used to set HTTP headers.

lvardefs.name: objRef
lvardefs.desc: Header elements would be used to set HTTP headers.

name: $requestId
desc: Returns: The fixture id (maybe new) to map to the request.

pvardefs.name: pValue
pvardefs.desc: The fixture id (maybe new) to map to the request.

name: $responseId
desc: Returns: The fixture id (maybe new) to map to the response.

pvardefs.name: pValue
pvardefs.desc: The fixture id (maybe new) to map to the response.

name: $sourceId
desc: Returns: The id of the fixture used as the body of a PUT or POST request.

pvardefs.name: pValue
pvardefs.desc: The id of the fixture used as the body of a PUT or POST request.

name: $targetId
desc: Returns: Id of fixture used for extracting the [id],  [type], and [vid] for GET requests.

pvardefs.name: pValue
pvardefs.desc: Id of fixture used for extracting the [id],  [type], and [vid] for GET requests.
